external_knowledge:
Initial model refers to the model with model_id = 0;
Detailed information includes version numbers, descriptions, and creation timestamps;
Latest iteration means the highest version number.

sql:
SELECT models.model_name
FROM models
WHERE models.model_id NOT IN (
  SELECT model_versions.model_id
  FROM model_versions
);

external_knowledge:
Highly precise models refer to those with a precision metric above 0.8; thoroughly worked on implies the training sessions are completed; and accessible for viewing means the access type is 'view'.;
Precision is a metric used in machine learning to measure the accuracy of positive predictions. A precision value above 0.8 is considered good, indicating that the model performs well in predicting positive cases.;
Training sessions reaching the 'completed' status signifies that the model has gone through the full training process and is ready for use.; 
Models with 'view' access can be inspected but not modified by other users.

sql:
SELECT description 
FROM models 
WHERE model_id IN (
  SELECT model_id 
  FROM bad_epochs
);
